parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag clock spring can prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag system fails to deploy in the event of a crash
the clock spring spiral cable fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause distraction, obstruct the driver's view, and lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without impact
airbags deploy while driving
airbags deploy without warning
airbag light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the airbag system can prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
airbag warning light illuminates
airbag system needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the passenger side airbag can prevent the airbag from deploying in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Passenger side airbag fails to deploy
passenger side airbag needs to be replaced
passenger side seat and airbag need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to fail to start, illuminate warning lights, and pose a risk of fire.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
warning lights illuminate on the dashboard
the radio turns on without the key in the ignition
and the vehicle remains running for a minute after the key is removed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause the rear tail lights to malfunction, posing a safety risk to other drivers.
symptoms: The rear tail lights do not work
and a burning odor is present in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the vehicle to experience parasitic draw, leading to battery drain and potential electrical system failure.
symptoms: The instrument cluster stays on when the keys are out of the vehicle
and the dash indicators flicker.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbags do not deploy in a crash
resulting in injury or near-miss.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear sonar system can cause a lack of visibility when reversing, posing a safety risk to pedestrians or other vehicles.
symptoms: The rear sonar system does not work
and the rear view monitor does not display.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cold Temperature-Related ABS and Traction Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS and traction control system at low temperatures can increase the risk of accidents, especially in cold climates.
symptoms: ABS light and traction control light illuminate upon starting the vehicle
disabling the ABS system and traction control system
and potentially disabling the 4-wheel drive system if not engaged before movement.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Bell Housing Failure and Drivetrain Vibration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the bell housing can cause drivetrain vibration, leading to potential damage to the transmission, driveshaft, and rear axles, and potentially causing loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Drivetrain vibration
cracks in the bell housing
transmission slipping
and potential disintegration of the bell housing.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping and loss of power can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving uphill or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Transmission slipping
loss of power
and inability to maintain speed
especially when driving uphill.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank venting issue can cause fuel to splash out of the filler neck during refueling, creating a hazardous situation and potentially leading to fires or explosions.
symptoms: Fuel shoots out of the filler neck when filling up
fuel splashes out of the receptacle after a short period of fueling
the auto shut-off on the fuel pump activates and refueling stops
but not before fuel splashes out
fuel spills all over the truck
the person refueling
and the ground.
